# Prototype 3 - News Navigator Timeline View

This prototype builds on the previous versions of the News Navigator platform, focusing on enhancing the user experience with timeline-based visualization and improved filtering features.

## Features

- Timeline-based news visualization showing news evolution over time
- Enhanced filtering capabilities for news articles
- Personalized news recommendations based on user preferences
- Improved article categorization and bias detection
- Responsive design for mobile and desktop viewing

## Technology Stack

- Flask (Python web framework) for backend services
- Jinja2 templates for server-side rendering
- JavaScript for interactive elements
- CSS for styling and responsive design

## Setup Instructions

1. Create a virtual environment:
   ```
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   ```
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

3. Run the application:
   ```
   python app.py
   ```

4. Open your browser and navigate to `http://localhost:5000`

